column2: Ok, lets start with the basics. What's your first name?
column4: Which state are you based in?
column7: Which industry is your startup in?
column8: How clear and well articulated is *the problem* that you're solving with your offering?
column9: How much does your solution easily demonstrate a clear customer value proposition? (zero means 'they don't get it' and 5 means 'they repeatedly come back for more')
column10: There a large and still growing market for your solution (zero means 'not at all' and 5 means 'huge and still growing rapidly')
column11: How much does your current business model/pricing strategy encourage repeat purchases/subscription vs. one-time transactional revenue generation? (zero means , 'not at all' and 5 means 'I have a full subscription models)
column12: How unique is your offering to what exists in the market? (zero means 'not at all' and 5 means 'no direct competitors')
column13: How soon do you envision revenue being generated? (zero means 'revenue? what's that?' and 5 means 'already generating and growing')
column14: How easy is it for a customer to purchase your offering (zero means 'long sales cycle & lots of steps to get to payment' and 5 means 'buy now & buy often')
column15: How easy is it to identify and to reach your paying customers? (zero means 'i think I know who they are and all I have to do is go knocking on their doors' and 5 means 'highly leveraged means to get to them')
column16: How much traction have you demonstrated to date? (zero means 'we haven't gotten out of the gate yet' and 5 means 'we have lots of engaged users, strong user growth, some (&  growing) monthly recurring revenue, formalized partnerships)
column17: How much have you done with respect to intellectual property? (zero means 'we don't need no stinkin' IP' and 5 means 'we have filed trademarks, copyrights &/or patents and are ready to defend them')
column18: How well do you know your competitors and believe you have a genuine competitive advantage? (zero means 'there are no competitors at all' and 5 means 'we understand all competitive offerings and believe we have a 'better mouse trap'')
column19: How many co-founders are there and do you/they have a solid track record in the subject matter of the business? (zero means 'I'm the solo founder and I've never worked in this space before' and 5 means 'all co-founders come from the space with strong experience')
column20: How strong are your advisors, investors and key professionals (e.g. lawyers, accountants, marketing agency)? (zero means 'we haven't raised any money from outsiders, haven't invited any advisors and don't have a lot to spend on key professionals' and 5 means 'we have some key, influential investors, an awesome, diverse advisory board and have great key professionals that work well with startups')
column21: Have you set up a stock option plan to attract key personnel and partners? (zero means 'what is a stock option plan?' and 5 means 'our attorneys have set up a formal stock option plan so that all of our (future) key hires are incentivized to help grow the business')
column22: How well do you understand your customer acquisition costs and the lifetime value of a customer? (zero means 'what do those things mean?' and 5 means 'we have calculated the and are tracking these things regularly')
column23: How detailed is your 3 year, bottom up financial forecast? (zero means 'oh, we need to do a 3 year forecast?' and 5 means 'what revenue stream or cost category would you like to discuss right now?')
column24: How long will your revenue or capital raised last given your monthly burn rate? (zero means 'OMG, we need a sale or an investor NOW' and 5 means 'we should be good for at least 15-18 months')
column25: How much traction have you had with prospective investors ? (zero means 'we've got lots of irons in the fire but no investment in our bank' and 5 means 'we've raised from some key, influential investors who have helped us secure others')
column26: How comfortable are prospective investors with the current valuation? (zero means 'no one's invested as they don't get how big we're going to be' and 5 means 'we did a crawl, walk, run raise where we started low, built some traction, achieved some milestones and then raised the next round')
column27: How ready are you with your due diligence documents? (zero means 'due who?' and 5 means 'just log in to our online deal room to access whatever you need to see')
column28: How well do you know potential acquirers and their history of acquiring companies in your space? (zero means 'not at all' and 5 means 'we're tracking all M&A activity in our space')
column29: How prepared are you to grow the business organically if you can't get acquired or IPO? (zero means 'we better get acquired or I'm not sure investors will make any money' and 5 means 'heck, we're ready to become the acquirer and consolidate the industry ourselves')
column30: How well connected are you in your industry? (zero means 'I'm new to the space but a bit of an introvert' and 5 means 'I'm a natural connector and my Rolodex is overflowing')
column31: How well do you communicate with visuals vs text? (zero means 'I'm a terrible artist!' and 5 means 'I'm a strong believer that a picture says a thousand words')
